                            now conſider thoſe which ſhe forms on the other parts of the Face.

The Voice becomes hoarſe by the inequality

of its organs;
The Voice is hoarſe. for heat melting the humors and making them run on thoſe parts, it renders them moiſt and unequal, and the voice which it utters is rude, and ſounds not; and becauſe that vehemency is joyned with this ſharpneſs thence it is it becomes terrible and frightfull.
